    <title>Hive algebras and tensor product algebras for small GL(n)</title>
    <summary>  For the complex general linear group GL(n), the GL(n) tensor product algebra
TA(n) introduced by Howe et al. describes the decomposition of the tensor
products of two irreducible polynomial representations of GL(n). Using the hive
model for the Littlewood-Richardson coefficients, we provide a finite
presentation of the algebra TA(n) for n=2, 3, 4 in terms of generators and
relations, thereby giving a description of highest weight vectors of
irreducible representations in the tensor products. We also compute the
generating function of certain sums of Littlewood-Richardson coefficients.
</summary>
